<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>42-406</num>
  <heading>First recorded deed preferred.</heading>
  <text>When 2 or more deeds of the same property are made to bona fide purchasers for value without notice, the deed or deeds which are first recorded according to law shall be preferred.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 56-2-ch854" path="§500">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1268, ch. 854, § 500</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 45-502.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 45-802.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
